external_knowledge:
More committed -> paid more than 5 premiums;
Highly rated -> application underwriting score > 750;
Specific channels -> channel B or channel E;
Track record of making multiple payments -> no_of_premiums_paid > 5.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) 
FROM payment_history 
WHERE count_more_than_12_months_late > 0;

SELECT COUNT(customer_id) AS Total_Customers
FROM risk_profiles
WHERE risk_score > 0.8;

SELECT AVG(age_in_days / 365) AS average_age_in_years
FROM customers
WHERE no_of_premiums_paid > 5;

external_knowledge:
- 'Mature adults' refers to customers aged between 25 and 35 years old; 
- 'Above the norm' means their income is higher than the average income of all customers who earn more than zero;
- 'Typical payment adjusted based on payment lateness' is the average payment amount from payment history records, modified by the cosine of the number of late payments.

sql:
SELECT risk_category, AVG(risk_score) AS average_score
FROM risk_profiles
GROUP BY risk_category;
